Special thanks to thn81, L42y, City-Busz, and all of the other AUR maintainers that helped make it possible to run Unity under Arch Linux!

Please make sure you don't already have modified versions of the dependencies installed. For example, qt-ubuntu might fail to compile if there's a modified version of qt already installed.

Packages ending with "-ubuntu" contain Ubuntu patches and REPLACE Arch Linux versions of those packages.

Order to compile/install:

01: glib2-ubuntu                   -> glib 2.0 with Ubuntu patches
02: inputproto-ubuntu              -> X11 input extension wire protocol
03: libxi-ubuntu                   -> X11 Input library with Ubuntu patches
04: gtk2-ubuntu                    -> GTK toolkit 2.0 with Ubuntu patches
05: gtk3-ubuntu                    -> GTK toolkit 3.0 with Ubuntu patches
06: gconf-ubuntu                   -> A configuration database system
07: qt-ubuntu                      -> Qt framework with Ubuntu patches
08: libdbusmenu                    -> Library for passing menus over DBus
09: libindicator                   -> Symbols and functions for indicators
10: libindicate                    -> Libraries for apps to raise 'flags' on DBus
11: libindicate-qt                 -> Qt bindings for libindicate
12: libappindicator                -> Library to export menu bar to Unity
13: appmenu-gtk                    -> Application menu module for GTK+
14: appmenu-qt                     -> Application menu support for QT
15: bamf                           -> Application matching framework
16: libqtbamf                      -> Qt bindings for bamf
17: dee                            -> Create Model-View-Controller apps over DBus
18: libqtdee                       -> Qt binding and QML plugin for Dee
19: libqtgconf                     -> Qt bindings for GConf
20: dconf-qt                       -> Qt bindings for DConf
21: sni-qt                         -> Turns Qt tray icons into appindicators
22: ido                            -> Widgets and objects used for indicators
23: libzeitgeist                   -> Client library to interact with Zeitgeist
24: python-rdflib                  -> A language for representing information
25: zeitgeist-datahub              -> Plugins that insert events into Zeitgeist
26: zeitgeist-datasources          -> Data sources for Zeitgeist
27: geoclue                        -> Modular geoinformation service
28: python-geoclue                 -> Geoclue Python module
29: python-xapian                  -> Python bindings for Xapian
30: zeitgeist-extensions           -> Extensions for Zeitgeist
31: gnome-activity-journal         -> Tool for easily browsing and finding files
32: gnome-settings-daemon-ubuntu   -> Daemon handling the GNOME session settings
33: gnome-session-ubuntu           -> GNOME Session Manager
34: gnome-control-center-ubuntu    -> Utilities to configure the GNOME desktop
35: gnome-screensaver-ubuntu       -> Screensaver and screen locking for GNOME
36: metacity-ubuntu                -> Lightweight GTK+ window manager
37: launchpad-integration          -> Launchpad.net integration
38: nautilus-ubuntu                -> File manager and graphics shell for GNOME
39: mutter-ubuntu                  -> Lightweight GTK+ window manager
40: indicator-applet               -> GNOME panel indicator applet
41: indicator-application          -> Takes menus and puts then in the panel
