47: indicator-sound                -> A unified sound menu
48: network-manager-applet-ubuntu  -> Network Manager applet with indicator support
49: gnome-bluetooth-ubuntu         -> Gnome bluetooth applet with indicator support
50: gtest                          -> C++ testing utility based on xUnit
51: gmock                          -> A library for writing C++ mock classes
52: nux                            -> An OpenGL toolkit
53: plasma-widget-menubar *        -> KDE Plasma widget to display menubar
54: xfce4-indicator-plugin *       -> XFCE panel plugin to display indicators
55: xorg-xinput-ubuntu             -> Command line tool to configure input devices
56: xorg-server-ubuntu             -> Xorg X11 server
57: xf86-video-intel-ubuntu *      -> Xorg X11 Intel video driver
58: xf86-video-nouveau-ubuntu *    -> Xorg X11 nVidia video driver
59: xf86-video-ati-ubuntu *        -> Xorg X11 ATI/AMD video driver
60: mtdev                          -> Multitouch protocol translation library
61: utouch-evemu                   -> Event emulation for the uTouch stack
62: utouch-frame                   -> Touch frame library
63: utouch-grail                   -> Gesture recognition and instantiation lib.
64: utouch-geis                    -> Implementation of the GEIS interface
65: xf86-input-evdev-ubuntu        -> Xorg X11 evdev input driver
66: xf86-input-synaptics-ubuntu *  -> Xorg X11 Synaptics touchpad driver
67: unity-asset-pool               -> Design assets for Unity
68: gnome-menus2                   -> Gnome menu specifications
69: libunity                       -> Library for integrating Unity
70: libunity-misc                  -> Differently licensed stuff for Unity
71: unity-lens-applications        -> Unity applications lens
72: unity-lens-files               -> Unity files lens
73: unity-lens-music               -> Unity music lens
74: compiz-core-ubuntu             -> Compiz core components
75: utouch-compiz                  -> Links uTouch with Compiz
76: libcompizconfig-ubuntu         -> Compiz configuration system library
77: compizconfig-backend-gconf-ubuntu * -> GConf backend for Compiz
78: compizconfig-backend-kconfig4-ubuntu * -> KConfig4 backend for Compiz
79: compizconfig-python-ubuntu     -> Compizconfig bindings for Python
80: ccsm-ubuntu                    -> Compiz configuration manager
81: compiz-plugins-main-ubuntu     -> Compiz main plugins
82: compiz-plugins-extra-ubuntu    -> Compiz extra plugins
83: unity-core *                   -> Parts of Unity 3D needed for Unity 2D
84: unity                          -> A desktop experience designed for efficiency
85: unity-2d                       -> 2D implementation of Unity

* Optional packages
  - plasma-widget-menubar          => For KDE users who want a global menubar
  - xfce4-indicator-plugin         => Ayatana indicators plugin for the XFCE panel
  - xf86-video-intel-ubuntu        => For users with Intel integrated graphics cards
  - xf86-video-nouveau-ubuntu      => For users with nVidia graphics cards
  - xf86-video-ati-ubuntu          => For users with ATI/AMD graphics cards
  - xf86-input-synaptics-ubuntu    => For users with a Synaptics touchpad (laptops)
  - compizconfig-backend-gconf-ubuntu => Store Compiz settings in GConf
  - compizconfig-backend-kconfig4-ubuntu => Store Compiz settings in KConfig4
  - unity-core                     => For users that want Unity 2D, but not Unity 3D

All of PKGBUILD's were checked by namcap for consistency. The binary packages have not been checked yet.

Troubleshooting:

Global menus aren't working when logging in with KDM (KDE display manager).

  This happens because previous versions of KDM weren't patched to source the
  /etc/X11/xinit/xinitrc.d/ directory. This is fixed in kdebase-workspace version
  4.7.2-1, but requires the KDM configuration files to be regenerated (resetting
  all KDM configuration options). To regenerate the configuration files, run as root

    # rm -rvf /usr/share/config/kdm
    # genkdmconf
